1.title: Launch Program
1.plot: Participants in the series attend answer questions from the audience about their educational journeys. Forum hosted by Annette Shun Wah.

2.title: Episode #1.2
2.plot: An Iranian refugee and the daughter of Vietnamese refugees tell how they overcame adversity to study computing and law respectively in Australia.

3.title: Episode #1.3
3.plot: Jayne's tenacity in becoming a vet eventually paid off, while George tells how higher education took him from the Australian Outback to the big smoke.

4.title: Episode #1.4
4.plot: Tanja and her family fled war-torn Bosnia for a new life in Australia, where she began studying a degree in Medical Science. Meanwhile, Corey is inspiring children to dream big after a successful rugby league career.

5.title: Episode #1.5
5.plot: Deng is using his law degree to help fellow Sudanese refugees now living in Australia, while Amy's career behind the wheel of a big rig is proving useful as the basis for study in engineering.

6.title: Episode #1.6
6.plot: Ross trades life in a war zone for shooting of a very different variety, while witnessing a debilitating illness in her family led Rita on the path to becoming a nurse.

7.title: Episode #1.7
7.plot: Scott had worked as everything from a fireman to a preacher, but eventually discovered his true passion lay in medicine. And after fleeing Afghanistan for Australia, Najeeba is determined to help fellow refugees through her studies.

8.title: Episode #1.8
8.plot: Asha fled her native Fiji for a new life - and a PhD - in Australia, while a serious health scare hasn't stopped Steven from pursuing a career in juvenile justice.

9.title: Episode #1.9
9.plot: Genna is studying nursing and has grand plans for a remote Kenyan village when she graduates. Robert's persistence and talent prove their worth in the world of mathematics.

10.title: Episode #1.10
10.plot: Suraya is making a difference to student's lives after fleeing Afghanistan for Australia, while Bradley's passion for journalism was ignited by a trip to a university summer school.

11.title: Episode #1.11
11.plot: Single mum Nicole is turning her life around through university education, while William's hard work has landed him a job at one of Australia's leading architectural firms.

imdb.plot outline: Models of Achievement is a compelling series that explores the success and aspirations of 20 Australians who changed their lives through higher education. Interviewees tell their stories in their own words, many from disadvantaged backgrounds, originally arriving in Australia as refugees, many uncertain of their career passion. The forum-style Models of Achievement Special Launch Episode moderated by Annette Shun Wah involves participants in a Q &A discussion on their educational journey. Models of Achievement proves it's never too late to change your life.
